On Sun, 9 May 2004 14:48:34 -0700 (PDT), Mitchell Timin
&lt;zenguyuno@...&gt; wrote:
&gt; Suppose I have no code, but just a paper sketch of an
&gt; ANN with some neurons, connections, inputs, outputs,
&gt; etc.  Can I describe it with XML and then generate the
&gt; graphics?

Sure...as long as the XML follows a format like this:

&lt;network&gt;
&lt;neuron id=&quot;0&quot; type=&quot;input&quot; hint-layer=&quot;1&quot; hint-position=&quot;1&quot;  /&gt;
&lt;neuron id=&quot;3&quot; type=&quot;output&quot; hint-layer=&quot;2&quot; hint-position=&quot;1&quot;  /&gt;
&lt;connection src-id=&quot;0&quot; tgt-id=&quot;3&quot; weight=&quot;0.08538433836400572&quot;
recurrent=&quot;false&quot; /&gt;
&lt;/network&gt;

You can just type it up, save it as &quot;network-whatever.xml&quot;, and use
the NEVT to parse it into SVG.

Derek
